## 1. Platform Overview\
\
### What Is This System?\
\
AviationMX is a **multi-tenant SaaS platform** where any organization \'97 a flight school like **Horizon Flights**, an MRO, an independent A&P shop, or a single aircraft owner \'97 can sign up, create their workspace, and manage:\
\
- Aircraft records (airframe, engines, propellers, avionics)\
- Maintenance logbooks (FAA Part 43-compliant entries)\
- Mechanic credentials (A&P certificates, IA authorizations, currency)\
- Team access control (who sees what aircraft, what books)\
- Shared document libraries (SBs, ADs, AMMs, catalog pages)\
\
### Core Tenets\
\
| Tenet | Description |\
|-------|-------------|\
| **Multi-tenancy** | Every organization is fully isolated; data never bleeds across accounts |\
| **Role hierarchy** | Owner \uc0\u8594  Admin \u8594  Mechanic (A&P / IA) \u8594  Sub-user (AMP / OJT) |\
| **Aircraft-centric** | Aircraft is the core object; all records attach to it |\
| **Owner controls access** | Aircraft owner always retains sovereignty; can grant/revoke at any time |\
| **Mechanic autonomy** | Mechanics can have their own standalone workspace AND link to owners |\
| **FAA-aware** | Certificate numbers, IA currency, Part 43 signing, 7-year retention built in |\
\
