### 5.2 Aircraft Ownership Rules\
\
- **First user to add an aircraft becomes its `primary_owner`** \'97 this is stored in the `aircraft` table and **cannot be changed by anyone except the platform** (in case of legitimate transfer)\
- The primary owner can:\
  - Grant access to others\
  - Revoke access from others\
  - Delete the aircraft (soft-delete, 30-day hold for audit)\
  - Transfer ownership (requires platform support ticket + verification)\
- Even if a mechanic has aircraft access, they can never delete or transfer it\
\
### 5.3 Aircraft Unique ID System\
\
Every aircraft gets two IDs:\
\
```\
aircraft_id  =  "acft_01HXK9..."     \uc0\u8592  Internal UUID (never shown to user)\
aircraft_uid =  "AX-N1234X-2018"     \uc0\u8592  Human-readable unique ID for sharing\
```\
\
The `aircraft_uid` (combining prefix + N-number + year) is what mechanics use to link aircraft cross-accounts. It is unique globally within the platform.\
\
