### 8.3 Entry Status Lifecycle\
\
```\
DRAFT \uc0\u8594  [mechanic working on it]\
  \uc0\u9474 \
  \uc0\u9660 \
PENDING_REVIEW \uc0\u8594  [OJT submitted, waiting for A&P countersign]\
  \uc0\u9474               [or: entry created, parts not yet confirmed]\
  \uc0\u9660 \
SIGNED \uc0\u8594  [A&P signed; legally binding; entry is now immutable]\
  \uc0\u9474 \
  \uc0\u9500 \u9472 \u9472 \u9658  COUNTERSIGNED (IA) \u8594  [Annual/Major Repair requiring IA sign-off]\
  \uc0\u9474 \
  \uc0\u9492 \u9472 \u9472 \u9658  ARCHIVED \u8594  [aircraft sold/decommissioned; read-only forever]\
```\
\
> **IMMUTABILITY RULE:** Once an entry status becomes `SIGNED`, no field may be edited. A new `AMENDMENT` entry must be created referencing the original entry_id.\
\
