## 15. Security & Compliance\
\
### 15.1 Authentication Security\
\
| Control | Implementation |\
|---------|----------------|\
| Password strength | Min 12 chars, uppercase + lowercase + number + special |\
| Password storage | bcrypt, cost factor 12 |\
| JWT secret | 256-bit random, rotated quarterly |\
| JWT expiry | 1 hour (access), 7 days (refresh) |\
| Session storage | Refresh tokens in httpOnly cookie |\
| Rate limiting | 5 failed logins \uc0\u8594  15 min lockout; 100 req/min per user |\
| MFA (future) | TOTP via Authenticator apps |\
\
### 15.2 Data Security\
\
| Control | Implementation |\
|---------|----------------|\
| Tenant isolation | Row-Level Security (PostgreSQL) |\
| Transport | TLS 1.3 mandatory |\
| Storage encryption | AES-256 at rest (S3 SSE-KMS) |\
| API auth | JWT Bearer tokens on all /api/* routes |\
| File uploads | Virus scan (ClamAV), file type whitelist |\
| SQL injection | Parameterized queries via Prisma/TypeORM |\
| XSS | Content-Security-Policy headers, output encoding |\
| CSRF | SameSite=Strict cookies, CSRF tokens on state-changing ops |\
\
### 15.3 FAA Compliance Requirements\
\
| Requirement | Implementation |\
|-------------|----------------|\
| Part 43 \'97 Record Format | Entry fields match required FAA format |\
| Part 43.9 \'97 Signature | Digital signature hash + certificate number stored |\
| Part 43.11 \'97 Approval | IA countersignature workflow for annual inspections |\
| Part 91.417 \'97 Retention | 7-year minimum retention; archive instead of delete |\
| Immutability | Signed entries are immutable; amendments create new records |\
| Audit trail | Every action logged with timestamp, user, IP |\
| Certificate validation | IA expiry checked before allowing countersignature |\
| Export | PDF export preserves all required fields + signatures |\
\
### 15.4 Access Revocation\
\
When an owner revokes a mechanic's aircraft access:\
\
```\
1. aircraft_access.status = "revoked"\
2. aircraft_access.revoked_at = now()\
3. aircraft_access.revoked_by_id = owner_user_id\
4. Mechanic immediately loses aircraft from their dashboard (next API call)\
5. All active sessions invalidated for that resource (cache cleared)\
6. Mechanic receives: "Your access to N1234X has been revoked."\
7. Audit log entry created\
8. All DRAFT entries by mechanic flagged: \uc0\u9888 \u65039  "Access revoked \'97 entry incomplete"\
9. All SIGNED entries remain intact (FAA requires permanence)\
```\
