## Appendix: Key Business Rules Summary\
\
| Rule | Details |\
|------|---------|\
| **Aircraft primary owner is permanent** | Cannot be changed without platform intervention |\
| **Owner always has full aircraft control** | No one can remove owner's own access to their aircraft |\
| **Signed entries are immutable** | Use amendment records for corrections |\
| **7-year retention** | No hard deletes on logbook entries ever |\
| **IA currency enforced** | System checks expiry before allowing IA countersignature |\
| **OJT entries require countersign** | Cannot be signed to "signed" status by OJT alone |\
| **Cross-org aircraft** | Only via explicit aircraft_access records; no org data bleeds |\
| **Invite tokens expire** | 30 days by default; must be resent after expiry |\
| **Revocation is immediate** | Cache invalidated; next API call enforces revocation |\
| **Community docs are read-only** | Users can save/link but not modify community library items |\
